# Get a free access key at https://web3forms.com (register the inbox that should receive submissions).
#
# Local: copy to `.env`, set the value, restart `npm run dev` (Vite embeds VITE_* at build time).
#
# Production (Vercel): Project → Settings → Environment Variables → add:
#   Name:  VITE_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY
#   Value: your key from web3forms.com
#   Apply to: Production (and Preview if you want forms on preview deploys)
# Then redeploy so the new env is baked into the client bundle.
#
# Without this variable, the contact form falls back to opening the user’s mail app.
VITE_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY=
